ionFailure will return false when it encounters a missing target. There’s a concern about whether an unsupported error in native contexts could be treated as a general Error rather than a LinkageError since existing functionality only catches LinkageError. It seems I may need to look into importing NativeImageSupport as an internal tck dependency.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for the active class `io.restassured.internal.RequestSpecificationImpl$_removeCookie_closure2`.\n\nAdded:\n\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io/restassured/internal/RequestSpecificationImplRemoveCookieClosure2Access.java`\n  - Helper to invoke the Groovy compiler-generated `class$` resolver for the active closure.\n\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/RequestSpecificationImplInner_removeCookie_closure2Test.java`\n  - Covers the remaining `Class#forName(String)` dynamic-access call site.\n  - Verifies missing-class behavior.\n  - Exercises public `removeCookie(String)` behavior, confirming case-insensitive cookie removal while preserving unrelated cookies.\n\nPer instruction, I did not run tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b7c467f9a487366016a01185051488197bc3e8e1a5ec6a109\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2470, "output": 700, "cacheRead": 46080, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49250, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778456647003, "responseId": "resp_0b7c467f9a487366016a0118478d688197acef51233f4a798c"}, "toolResults": []}
